{"author":"Joe Oakhart","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Context\nStamp denormalized author identity (name + email) plus an OPTIONAL `author_id`\n(referencing a ddbe `identity`) onto EVERY mutating event's envelope, without\nbreaking replay of pre-change events. Substrate for authorship attestation (bde5)\nand enforcement (3183). Hard-depends on ddbe (identity entity + resolver).\n\n## Why\nAuthorship certification needs each event to record who wrote it in a replication-\nand compaction-durable form (denormalized), with an optional link to the rich\n`identity` entity when one resolves (identity is opt-in).\n\n## What\n### 1. Shared attribution helper (`src/rebar/_commands/_seam.py`)\n- Extract `_git_config(key, fallback=\"\") -> str` from the existing `author()`;\n  reimplement `author()` on it; add `author_email()` = `_git_config(\"user.email\",\"\")`.\n  Strip; return fallback on unset / OSError / non-zero exit / timeout; NEVER raise.\n- Add `attribution_fields(repo_root=None) -> dict` returning\n  `{\"author_email\": author_email()}` plus `{\"author_id\": <id>}` ONLY when\n  `identity.resolve_current_identity(repo_root=repo_root)` is non-None (ddbe ships\n  this keyword-only `(*, repo_root=None)` signature; 4e9d depends on ddbe). Omit\n  `author_id` when None.\n- CACHE: a module-level dict `_ATTRIBUTION_CACHE: dict[str, dict]` keyed by the\n  RESOLVED repo_root string (NOT `lru_cache(maxsize=1)` — a single slot poisons\n  multi-repo tests). First call per repo_root does exactly ONE git-email lookup and\n  ONE `resolve_current_identity` scan; subsequent calls for that repo_root return the\n  cached dict. (Process-scoped; never persisted. A test helper may clear it.)\n\n### 2. Stamp at ALL FOUR envelope-composing sites (verified complete list)\nEvery site that COMPOSES an event envelope stamps `author` (name) next to `env_id`.\nAdd an optional `attribution: dict | None = None` parameter to each composer and do\n`if attribution: event.update(attribution)` immediately after the `author` key, so\n`author_email`/`author_id` land in the envelope. Callers pass\n`attribution_fields(repo_root)` computed WHERE they already compute/hold `author`\nand have `repo_root`/tracker in scope. The four sites:\n- `_seam.py::append_event` (lines ~219-220) — the majority path (create/edit/link/\n  comment/tag/sign/...). Compute `attribution_fields(repo_root)` inline (it already\n  receives `repo_root`); include it BEFORE the batch-sink branch so buffered events\n  are byte-identical.\n- `_commands/txn.py` — `transition_core` (STATUS ~280) and `claim_core` (STATUS ~449,\n  EDIT ~468). Add an `attribution: dict | None = None` kwarg to BOTH cores (mirroring\n  how `author`/`env_id` are already threaded); the callers `transition_close.py` and\n  `claim.py` (which hold `repo_root`) compute it and pass it. Do NOT add a bare\n  `repo_root` to the core signatures — thread the ready-made `attribution` dict.\n- `_commands/delete.py` — `_write_unlink` (~116) and `_write_event` (~206). Add an\n  `attribution: dict | None = None` param to both; their caller (which computes the\n  `author` string and holds the tracker/repo_root) passes `attribution_fields(...)`.\n- `_commands/compact.py` — SNAPSHOT composition in `_compact_locked` (~198) and\n  `rebuild_snapshot_from_full_log` (~364), which use `_git_author()`. Compute\n  `attribution_fields(repo_root)` alongside and merge it, so SNAPSHOTs carry\n  attribution too (otherwise a compacted ticket's fold loses it).\n\n### 3. Replay back-compat (reducer surfaces PRESENT-ONLY, matching where `author` lives)\nSurface present-only (mirrors `source_*`) at the SAME structural location each\nprocessor already puts `author` — verified sites:\n- `process_create` (_processors.py:59) → TOP-LEVEL `state[\"author_email\"]`/\n  `state[\"author_id\"]` present-only (the ticket-author attribution bde5 reads).\n- `process_comment` (:248) → on the per-comment `_entry` dict.\n- `process_revert` (:374) → on the per-revert record.\n- `process_signature` (:494) → on the signature record.\n(`process_edit`/`process_status` do NOT stamp author; NOT touched.) A pre-change\nevent (no author_email/author_id) reduces BYTE-IDENTICAL — no new keys anywhere.\nSNAPSHOT restores compiled_state verbatim (additive; older reducers ignore unknown\nkeys) — no special handling.\n\n## Scope\nIn: helpers + repo-keyed cache; stamping at the 4 composer sites via the\n`attribution` param; reducer present-only surfacing at the 4 processors; back-compat\n+ every-path + cache tests. Out: signing/verifying (bde5), key lifecycle (e165),\nenforcement (3183). `author_id` is populated, NOT verified/required here.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] EVERY mutating path stamps `author_email` into the raw stored event: a test\n  exercises `create` (append_event), `comment` (append_event), a `claim`/`transition`\n  (txn.py), a `delete`/archive (delete.py), and a `compact` SNAPSHOT (compact.py),\n  asserting each resulting event JSON contains `author_email` — proving all four\n  composers stamp it, not just append_event.\n- [ ] With a current identity set (`rebar identity use <id>`): a CREATE carries\n  `author_id == <id>` in the raw event AND top-level reduced state surfaces\n  `author_id`/`author_email`. With NO identity resolved: `author_id` is ABSENT from\n  both the raw event and reduced state (test both branches).\n- [ ] Back-compat: a hand-authored event stream WITHOUT author_email/author_id reduces\n  without error to compiled state containing NEITHER key anywhere (top-level or\n  sub-records) — byte-identical to pre-change — asserted by diffing the reduced dict.\n- [ ] `author_email()` returns `\"\"` (never raises) when `git config user.email` is\n  unset or the git call errors — tested by forcing the subprocess to fail.\n- [ ] Caching: across N sequential writes in one process for one repo_root, BOTH the\n  git-email lookup AND `resolve_current_identity` run at most once each — asserted with\n  TWO independent call-counters.\n\n## file_impact\n- `src/rebar/_commands/_seam.py` (_git_config + author_email + attribution_fields + repo-keyed cache + append_event stamping)\n- `src/rebar/_commands/txn.py` (attribution kwarg on transition_core + claim_core; callers compute it)\n- `src/rebar/_commands/delete.py` (attribution param on _write_unlink + _write_event)\n- `src/rebar/_commands/compact.py` (stamp SNAPSHOT envelopes in _compact_locked + rebuild_snapshot_from_full_log)\n- `src/rebar/reducer/_processors.py` (present-only surfacing: top-level at process_create; per-entry at comment/revert/signature)"}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783823474038580001,"uuid":"966c8994-76fb-45cf-9775-8fdc0bc101d1"}